-- Turkey’s Dogus Buys Maya Residence Offices, Gym, HT Reports
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-01-24T07:00:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/turkey-s-dogus-buys-maya-residence-offices-gym-ht-reports.html
Dogus Holding AS bought the shops,
sports and commercial spaces in Istanbul’s Maya Residences
complex, extending billionaire owner Ferit Sahenk’s reach into
the sports and entertainment field,  Haberturk  reported.  The purchase includes 23 shops, three movie screens and an
office as well as a sports center that has been converted into
the Dogus brand, D-Gym, the newspaper reported.  The investment follows Sahenk’s expansion into the food and
drink business with investments in Turkish restaurant chains
Nusr-ET, Lacivert and Kosebasi, Haberturk said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
